(3,'Unit 3: Animal','/uploads/2024/07/07/1720338480_Potato cake.jpg','Unit 3',1,1,NULL,NULL,'2024-08-10 11:30:13','3',40,'<p><strong>1.Short form: \'s/is</strong><br>1.1 Use \'s for speaking:<br>He is = He\'s&nbsp;<br>She is = She\'s<br>It is = It\'s<br>1.2 &nbsp;Use is/ isn\'t for questions and short answers:<br>Is she/he/it in Hanoi?<br>Yes, she/he/it is<br>No, she/he/it isn\'t</p><p>2. Key expressions: Starting a phone call<br><br><strong>2.1 Starting a call</strong><br>Good morning/afternoon. Hello / Hi.<br><strong>2.2 Answering a call</strong><br>Good morning, (company name).<br>(Yang) speaking.<br><br><strong>2.3 Asking for someone</strong><br>Can I speak to (Mr.Tang), please?<br>Hello. Is (Yelly) there?<br>Is (Vivian) in the office?<br>Is that (Lisa)?<br><strong>2.4 Saying \'yes\'</strong><br>Yes, of course. (One moment.)<br>Sure. (One moment.)<br><br><strong>2.5 Saying \'no\'</strong><br>No, I\'m sorry, she\'s not in<br>the office.<br>No, I\'m sorry, he\'s out.<br>No, it isn\'t. It\'s (Clara).<br><strong>2.6 Ending a call</strong><br>OK. Thanks.<br>Goodbye.</p>'),
